<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=332&amp;p=2221#p2221"><![CDATA[
This looks like little more than a zipped Pasofami format, except using UNIF-style board names. Personally, I'm against it, since it would <strong>require</strong> implementing ZIP support in order to even load them, and it does not provide any advantage whatsoever over UNIF (in fact, it would be arguably <em>worse</em>, since zipped UNIF would compress better anyways).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Thu Jun 02, 2005 12:28 pm</p><hr />
